  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Key Enforcement Agencies:\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- National financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Banking regulators\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and enforcement mechanisms.",
